The paper discusses the properties of data representations learned by deep neural networks, which is a common topic in the field of machine learning. The focus on intrinsic dimensionality is particularly relevant to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the most likely category. The use of neural networks for image classification (as mentioned in the abstract) suggests that the paper could also be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the use of neural networks for classification tasks suggests that the paper could be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the mention of classification accuracy suggests that the paper could also be relevant to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
